#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:40
msgid "1. Using arbitrary objects in NumPy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:42
msgid ""
"The first set of interoperability features from the NumPy API allows foreign "
"objects to be treated as NumPy arrays whenever possible. When NumPy "
"functions encounter a foreign object, they will try (in order):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:46
msgid ""
"The buffer protocol, described :py:doc:`in the Python C-API documentation "
"<python:c-api/buffer>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:48
msgid ""
"The ``__array_interface__`` protocol, described :ref:`in this page <arrays."
"interface>`. A precursor to Python's buffer protocol, it defines a way to "
"access the contents of a NumPy array from other C extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:52
msgid ""
"The ``__array__()`` method, which asks an arbitrary object to convert itself "
"into an array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:55
msgid ""
"For both the buffer and the ``__array_interface__`` protocols, the object "
"describes its memory layout and NumPy does everything else (zero-copy if "
"possible). If that's not possible, the object itself is responsible for "
"returning a ``ndarray`` from ``__array__()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:60
msgid ""
":doc:`DLPack <dlpack:index>` is yet another protocol to convert foreign "
"objects to NumPy arrays in a language and device agnostic manner. NumPy "
"doesn't implicitly convert objects to ndarrays using DLPack. It provides the "
"function `numpy.from_dlpack` that accepts any object implementing the "
"``__dlpack__`` method and outputs a NumPy ndarray (which is generally a view "
"of the input object's data buffer). The :ref:`dlpack:python-spec` page "
"explains the ``__dlpack__`` protocol in detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:69
msgid "``dtype`` interoperability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:70
msgid ""
"Similar to ``__array__()`` for array objects, defining ``__numpy_dtype__`` "
"allows a custom dtype object to be interoperable with NumPy. The "
"``__numpy_dtype__`` must return a NumPy dtype instance (note that ``np."
"float64`` is not a dtype instance, ``np.dtype(np.float64)`` is)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/basics.interoperability.rst:75
msgid ""
"Before NumPy 2.4 a ``.dtype`` attribute was treated similarly. As of NumPy "
"2.4 both is accepted and implementing ``__numpy_dtype__`` prevents ``."
"dtype`` from being checked."
msgstr ""

